ZCZC OE72
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 032300 UTC
THIS PERIOD SHOULD START WITH A LOW IN THE CENTRAL
ATLANTIC WHICH WILL DEEPEN AS IT MOVS NE FALLING TO 987
MIDDAY SATURDAY THEN SLWY FLN 997 IN BAILEY MIDDAY
SUNDAY.
WINDS WILL BE RELATIVELY LIGHT ACROSS PORTPATRICK DURING
FRIDAY NIGHT INTO SATURDAY HOWEVER THE DEVELOPING
ATLANTIC LOW WILL STRENGTHEN WINDS IN ROCKALL AND NERN
SHANNON DURING SATURDAY MORNING. REACHING GALE FORCE AT
TIMES IN ROCKALL AND NERN SHANNON LATER EXTENDING INTO
MALIN HEBRIDES AND BAILEY AND AFFECTING IRISH SEA AT
TIMES. AS THE LOW MOVS NWARDS ON SATURDAY NIGHT STRG SE
WINDS WILL ALSO DEVELOP IN FAIR ISLE FAEROES AND S E
ICELAND. THROUGH SUNDAY WINDS WILL EASE FURTHER N BUT
STRG WINDS AND GALES WILL PERSIST THROUGH ROCKALL MALIN
AND NERN SHANNON. AFFECTING SERN PARTS OF BAILEY AND
HEBRIDES AT TIMES. DURING MONDAY STRG TO GALE FORCE WINDS
MAY AFFECT THE WHOLE OF PORTPATRICK AT TIMES ESPECIALLY
SEA AREAS FURTHER NW WHERE THERE IS A RISK OF SEV GALES
AT TIMES.
